E-commerce is always categorised as one of the fastest growing sector as nowadays most of the customers prefer to purchase online. In the case i have analysed customers are shopping via, App, Patrner App, Instagram,Target.com and Website.
I  Identified the Key Performance Indicators, which include;
       - Total orders
         - Total Amount
        -Avg. Rating
          Avg .Days to Deliver( ship date - Order date)
Vivo Califa's leadership wanted answers to 8 core business questions from three months of order data (Jan–Mar 2025):
        What's the order trend over the last 13 weeks?
        How do customers prefer to buy — app, website, or partner channels?
        How many items do customers typically buy per order?
        Which products are most popular?
        What's the overall gender split of buyers?
        Where (which CA counties) do customers live?
        How long does it take to ship orders?
         How happy are customers, based on ratings?
Each question was answered on its own PivotTable sheet, then the key results were brought together into one interactive dashboard.
Total Orders   2,400
Total Units Sold    11,997
Total Revenue   $649,019.80  
Average Customer Rating   4.0 
Average Days to Deliver  2.3 days


🔍 Key Insights
   Geography is concentrated: Los Angeles County alone drives $215,551 in revenue — roughly 33% of total sales — followed by San Diego County at $98,367.
   Mobile-first customers: The App is the top order channel (35% of sales), ahead of Website (24%), Target.com (18%), Partner App (12%), and Instagram (11%).
   Female customers lead: Of all units sold, 52% went to female customers, 39% to male, and the rest split between "Other" and "Unknown."
  T-Shirts and Jeans are the bestsellers, followed by Sneakers, Tank Tops, and Bikinis.
  Shipping is fast: 37% of all orders are delivered in just 1 day, and the vast majority ship within 3 days.
  Customers are happy: Roughly 3 in 4 orders receive a 4- or 5-star rating, consistent across January, February, and March.
  Small basket sizes: Most orders contain 1–3 items, with 2-item orders being the single most common basket size.


      
